      "content": "Cutting your insulin dose in half is not a safe way to go, as it can still lead to hypoglycemia. It's better to take your insulin as prescribed and adjust your food intake accordingly. If you skip your dose or cut it in half, you risk going low and ending up in the ER, which is not the safest option. Instead, eat something with a bit more sugar or carbohydrates, and then take your insulin as usual. And remember, it's always a good idea to consult with your healthcare team about any concerns you have regarding your insulin dose. They can provide guidance and help you find a safe way to manage your blood sugar.",
